101 {
102  QwtRoundScaleDraw *scaleDraw = new QwtRoundScaleDraw();
103  scaleDraw->setSpacing( 8 );

105  scaleDraw->setTickLength( QwtScaleDiv::MinorTick, 0 );
106  scaleDraw->setTickLength( QwtScaleDiv::MediumTick, 4 );
107  scaleDraw->setTickLength( QwtScaleDiv::MajorTick, 8 );
108  setScaleDraw( scaleDraw );
109 
110  setWrapping( false );
111  setReadOnly( true );
112 
113  setOrigin( 135.0 );
114  setScaleArc( 0.0, 270.0 );
115 
116

118  QwtDialSimpleNeedle::Arrow, true, Qt::red,
119  QColor( Qt::gray ).light( 130 ) );

134 // Reloaded virtual function - needed to display units label (RPM)
135 void SpeedoMeter::drawScaleContents( QPainter *painter,
136  const QPointF &center, double radius ) const
137 {
138  QRectF rect( 0.0, 0.0, 2.0 * radius, 2.0 * radius - 10.0 );
139  rect.moveCenter( center );
140 
141  const QColor color = palette().color( QPalette::Text );
142  painter->setPen( color );
143 
144  const int flags = Qt::AlignBottom | Qt::AlignHCenter;
145  painter->drawText( rect, flags, d_label );
146 }

150 WheelBox::WheelBox( Qt::Orientation orientation, double minv, double maxv, QString label, bool log, QWidget *parent ): QWidget( parent )
151 {
152  QWidget *box = createBox( orientation, minv, maxv, log );
153  d_label = new QLabel( this );
154  d_label->setAlignment( Qt::AlignHCenter | Qt::AlignTop );
155  d_label->setStyleSheet("font: bold;color: black;");

165 
166 QWidget *WheelBox::createBox( Qt::Orientation orientation, double minv, double maxv, bool log )
167 {
168  d_thermo = new QwtThermo();
169  d_thermo->setOrientation( orientation );
170 
171  d_thermo->setScalePosition( QwtThermo::TrailingScale );
172 
173  QwtLinearColorMap *colorMap = new QwtLinearColorMap();
174  colorMap->setColorInterval( Qt::blue, Qt::red );
175  d_thermo->setColorMap( colorMap );
176 
177  double min = minv;
178  double max = maxv;
179 
180  if ( log )
181  {
182  QwtLogScaleEngine* scaleengine = new QwtLogScaleEngine;
183  scaleengine->setAttribute(QwtScaleEngine::Floating,true);
184 
185  d_thermo->setScaleMaxMajor( 10 );
186  d_thermo->setScaleMaxMinor( 10 );
187  d_thermo->setScaleEngine( scaleengine );
188 
189  d_thermo->setScale( min + 0.5, max );
190  d_thermo->setValue( min );
191 
192  }
193  else
194  {
195  d_thermo->setScale( min, max );
196  d_thermo->setValue( min );
197  }
198 
199  QWidget *box = new QWidget();
200  QBoxLayout *layout;
201  layout = new QVBoxLayout( box );
202 
203  layout->addWidget( d_thermo, Qt::AlignCenter );
204 
205  return box;
206 }
207 
208 void WheelBox::setTemp( double v, QString label )

211  d_thermo->setValue( v );
212 
213  setNum( v, label );
214 }
215 
216 void WheelBox::setNum( double v, QString label )
217 {
218  //text = "Temp.: " + QString::number( v, 'f', 1 ) + QChar(0x2103);
219  QStringList labellist = label.split(",");
220 
221  QString text;
222  text = labellist[0] + " ";
223  if ( labellist[0].contains("Temp") )
224  text += QString::number( v, 'f', 1 ) + labellist[1];
225  else
226  text += QString::number( static_cast<int>(v) ) + labellist[1];;
227 
228  d_label->setText( text );
229 }

1373 // Slot to read all Optima machines <------------------------------- // New
1374 void US_XpnDataViewer::read_optima_machines( US_DB2* db )
1375 {
1376  QStringList q( "" );
1377  q.clear();
1378  q << QString( "get_instrument_names" )
1379  << QString::number( 1 );
1380  db->query( q );
1381 
1382  if ( db->lastErrno() == US_DB2::OK ) // If not, no instruments defined
1383  {
1384  QList< int > instrumentIDs;
1385 
1386  // Grab all the IDs so we can reuse the db connection
1387  while ( db->next() )
1388  {
1389  int ID = db->value( 0 ).toString().toInt();
1390  instrumentIDs << ID;
1391 
1392  qDebug() << "InstID: " << ID;
1393  }
1394 
1395  // Instrument information
1396  foreach ( int ID, instrumentIDs )
1397  {
1398  QMap<QString,QString> instrument;
1399 
1400  q.clear();
1401  q << QString( "get_instrument_info_new" )
1402  << QString::number( ID );
1403  db->query( q );
1404  db->next();
1405 
1406  instrument[ "ID" ] = QString::number( ID );
1407  instrument[ "name" ] = db->value( 0 ).toString();
1408  instrument[ "serial" ] = db->value( 1 ).toString();
1409  instrument[ "optimaHost" ] = db->value( 5 ).toString();
1410  instrument[ "optimaPort" ] = db->value( 6 ).toString();
1411  instrument[ "optimaDBname" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
1412  instrument[ "optimaDBusername" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();
1413  instrument[ "optimaDBpassw" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
1414  instrument[ "selected" ] = db->value( 10 ).toString();
1415 
1416  instrument[ "opsys1" ] = db->value( 11 ).toString();
1417  instrument[ "opsys2" ] = db->value( 12 ).toString();
1418  instrument[ "opsys3" ] = db->value( 13 ).toString();
1419 
1420  instrument[ "radcalwvl" ] = db->value( 14 ).toString();
1421  instrument[ "chromoab" ] = db->value( 15 ).toString();
1422 
1423  instrument[ "msgPort" ] = db->value( 16 ).toString();
1424 
1425  if ( instrument[ "name" ].contains("Optima") || instrument[ "optimaHost" ].contains("AUC_DATA_DB") )
1426  this->instruments << instrument;
1427  }
1428  }
1429  qDebug() << "Reading Instrument: FINISH in xpn_viewer";
1430 }

1432 // Slot to select in Optima in use <----------------------- // New
1433 void US_XpnDataViewer::changeOptima( int ndx )
1434 {
1435  cb_optima->setCurrentIndex( ndx );
1436  QString coptima = cb_optima->currentText();
1437  QString descr = coptima.section( ":", 1, 1 ).simplified();
1438 
1439  for ( int ii = 0; ii < instruments.size(); ii++ )
1440  {
1441  QString name = instruments[ii][ "name" ].trimmed();
1442  if ( name == descr )
1443  currentInstrument = instruments[ii];
1444  }
1445 
1446  xpndesc = currentInstrument[ "name" ];
1447  xpnhost = currentInstrument[ "optimaHost" ];
1448  xpnport = currentInstrument[ "optimaPort" ];
1449  xpnname = currentInstrument[ "optimaDBname" ];
1450  xpnuser = currentInstrument[ "optimaDBusername" ];
1451  xpnpasw = currentInstrument[ "optimaDBpassw" ];
1452 
1453  xpnmsgPort = currentInstrument[ "msgPort" ];
1454 
1455  test_optima_connection();
1456 
1457 }

1459 // sysserver conneciton
1460 //bool US_XpnDataViewer::check_sysdata_connection( Link* link1 )
1461 bool US_XpnDataViewer::check_sysdata_connection( void )
1462 {
1463  Link *link1 = new Link( xpndesc );
1464  //Link *link1 = new Link();
1465  bool status_sys_data = link1->connectToServer( xpnhost, xpnmsgPort.toInt() );
1466 
1467  qDebug() << "in [check_sysdata_connection]: status_sys_data: " << status_sys_data;
1468 
1469  //US_Sleep::msleep( 400 );
1470 
1471  link1->disconnectFromServer();
1472 
1473  bool combined_check = status_sys_data & link1->connected_itself;
1474 
1475  qDebug() << "status_sys_data & connected_itself = ? " << status_sys_data << " & " << link1->connected_itself << " = " << combined_check;
1476 
1477  delete link1;
1478 
1479  if ( !combined_check )
1480  {
1481  QMessageBox msgBox_sys_data;
1482  msgBox_sys_data.setIcon(QMessageBox::Critical);
1483  msgBox_sys_data.setWindowTitle(tr("Optima System Data Server Connection Problem!"));
1484 
1485  QString msg_sys_text = QString("Attention! UltraScan is not able to communicate with the data acquisition server on the %1. Please check the following: ").arg(xpndesc);
1486  QString msg_sys_text_info = QString("1. %1 is turned on \n2. the data acquisition server on %1 is running \n3. your license key is stored in $HOME/ultrascan/etc/optima and is not expired \n\nUse of the Optima Data Viewer is suspended until this condition is resolved. \n\nYou may check other Optima machines for proper conneciton.").arg(xpndesc);
1487 
1488  QPushButton *Accept_sys = msgBox_sys_data.addButton(tr("OK"), QMessageBox::YesRole);
1489 
1490  msgBox_sys_data.setText( msg_sys_text );
1491 
1492  msgBox_sys_data.setInformativeText( msg_sys_text_info );
1493 
1494  msgBox_sys_data.exec();
1495 
1496  if (msgBox_sys_data.clickedButton() == Accept_sys)
1497  {
1498  qDebug() << "Closing Program...";
1499 
1500  //this->close();
1501  }
1502 
1503  }
1504 
1505  //return status_sys_data;
1506  return combined_check;
1507 
1508 }

1510 //Slot to test Optima connection when Optima selection changed <------------- //New
1511 void US_XpnDataViewer::test_optima_connection()
1512 {
1513 
1514  qDebug() << "Optima in use: name, host, port, dbname, dbuser, dbpasw: " << xpndesc << " " << xpnhost << " "
1515  << xpnport << " " << xpnname << " " << xpnuser << " " << xpnpasw ;
1516 
1517 
1518  QPalette orig_pal = le_optima_connected->palette();
1519 
1520  if ( xpnhost.isEmpty() || xpnport.isEmpty()
1521  || xpnname.isEmpty() || xpnuser.isEmpty() || xpnpasw.isEmpty() )
1522  {
1523  le_optima_connected->setText( "disconnected" );
1524  QPalette *new_palette = new QPalette();
1525  new_palette->setColor(QPalette::Text,Qt::red);
1526  new_palette->setColor(QPalette::Base, orig_pal.color(QPalette::Base));
1527  le_optima_connected->setPalette(*new_palette);
1528 
1529  return;
1530  }
1531 
1532  US_XpnData* xpn_data1 = new US_XpnData();
1533  bool o_connected = xpn_data1->connect_data( xpnhost, xpnport.toInt(), xpnname, xpnuser, xpnpasw );
1534  xpn_data1->close();
1535  delete xpn_data1;
1536 
1537  if ( o_connected )
1538  {
1539  le_optima_connected->setText( "connected" );
1540  QPalette *new_palette = new QPalette();
1541  new_palette->setColor(QPalette::Text, Qt::darkGreen);
1542  new_palette->setColor(QPalette::Base, orig_pal.color(QPalette::Base));
1543  le_optima_connected->setPalette(*new_palette);
1544  }
1545  else
1546  {
1547  le_optima_connected->setText( "disconnected" );
1548  QPalette *new_palette = new QPalette();
1549  new_palette->setColor(QPalette::Text,Qt::red);
1550  new_palette->setColor(QPalette::Base, orig_pal.color(QPalette::Base));
1551  le_optima_connected->setPalette(*new_palette);
1552  }
1553 }

1598 // Enable the common dialog controls based on the presence of data
1599 void US_XpnDataViewer::enableControls( void )
1600 {
1601  const QChar chlamb( 955 );
1602 
1603  if ( allData.size() == 0 )
1604  { // If no data yet, just reset
1605  reset();
1606  return;
1607  }
1608 
1609  // Enable and disable controls now
1610  pb_loadXpn ->setEnabled( false );
1611  pb_loadAUC ->setEnabled( false );
1612  pb_reset ->setEnabled( true );
1613  pb_details ->setEnabled( true );
1614  pb_reload ->setEnabled( true );
1615  cb_cellchn ->setEnabled( true );
1616  cb_rstart ->setEnabled( true );
1617  cb_rend ->setEnabled( true );
1618  cb_pltrec ->setEnabled( true );
1619  pb_prev ->setEnabled( true );
1620  pb_next ->setEnabled( true );
1621  pb_plot2d ->setEnabled( true );
1622  pb_saveauc ->setEnabled( true );
1623  pb_showtmst->setEnabled( haveTmst );
1624 // pb_movie2d->setEnabled( true );
1625  ct_from ->setEnabled( true );
1626  ct_to ->setEnabled( true );
1627  pb_exclude ->setEnabled( true );
1628 
1629  ncellch = cellchans.count();
1630  nlambda = lambdas .count();
1631  ntriple = triples .count();
1632  nscan = allData[ 0 ].scanCount();
1633  npoint = allData[ 0 ].pointCount();
1634  ntpoint = nscan * npoint;
1635  int ktrip = ncellch * nlambda;
1636  isMWL = ( nlambda > 2 && ntriple == ktrip && ntriple > 48 );
1637  cb_cellchn ->setEnabled( isMWL );
1638 
1639 DbgLv(1) << "ec: ncc nwl nsc npt ntpt" << ncellch << nlambda << nscan
1640  << npoint << ntpoint << "Mwl" << isMWL;
1641 DbgLv(1) << "ec: npoint" << npoint << "radsize" << r_radii.count();
1642 DbgLv(1) << "ec: nlambda" << nlambda << "lmbsize" << lambdas.count();
1643 DbgLv(1) << "ec: ntriple" << ntriple << "trpsize" << triples.count() << "ktrip" << ktrip;
1644  QStringList slrads;
1645  QStringList sllmbs;
1646  QStringList plrecs;
1647 
1648  for ( int jj = 0; jj < npoint; jj++ )
1649  slrads << QString().sprintf( "%.3f", r_radii[ jj ] );
1650 
1651  for ( int jj = 0; jj < nlambda; jj++ )
1652  sllmbs << QString::number( lambdas[ jj ] );
1653 
1654  if ( isMWL )
1655  {
1656  prectype = ptype_mw;
1657  plrecs = sllmbs;
1658  }
1659  else
1660  {
1661  prectype = ptype_tr;
1662  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ntriple; jj++ )
1663  plrecs << QString( triples[ jj ] ).replace( " ", "" );
1664  }
1665 
1666  lb_pltrec->setText( prectype );
1667  connect_ranges( false );
1668  cb_cellchn->clear();
1669  cb_rstart ->clear();
1670  cb_rend ->clear();
1671  cb_pltrec ->clear();
1672 
1673  cb_cellchn->addItems( cellchans );
1674  cb_rstart ->addItems( slrads );
1675  cb_rend ->addItems( slrads );
1676  cb_pltrec ->addItems( plrecs );
1677 
1678  if ( nlambda == 1 )
1679  le_lrange ->setText( sllmbs[ 0 ] + tr( " only" ) );
1680  else if ( nlambda > 1 )
1681  le_lrange ->setText( sllmbs[ 0 ] + tr( " to " )
1682  + sllmbs[ nlambda - 1 ] );
1683 
1684  cb_cellchn->setCurrentIndex( 0 );
1685  cb_rstart ->setCurrentIndex( 0 );
1686  cb_rend ->setCurrentIndex( npoint - 1 );
1687  connect_ranges( true );
1688 
1689  have_rngs = false;
1690  compute_ranges( );
1691 
1692  ct_from ->setMaximum( nscan );
1693  ct_to ->setMaximum( nscan );
1694  cb_pltrec ->setCurrentIndex( nlambda / 2 );
1695  qApp->processEvents();
1696 
1697 DbgLv(1) << "ec: call changeCellCh";
1698  changeCellCh(); // Force a plot initialize
1699 }

2748 // Function to convert from a time in sec. to days, hours, minutes, seconds
2749 void US_XpnDataViewer::timeToList( int& sectime, QList< int >& dhms )
2750 {
2751  int t_day = (int)( sectime / (24*3600) );
2752  sectime -= t_day * 24 * 3600;
2753 
2754  int t_hour = (int)( sectime / 3600 );
2755  sectime -= t_hour * 3600;
2756 
2757  int t_minute = (int)( sectime / 60 );
2758  sectime -= t_minute * 60;
2759 
2760  int t_second = sectime;
2761 
2762  qDebug() << "TimeToList(): DD: " << t_day;
2763  qDebug() << "TimeToList(): HH: " << t_hour;
2764  qDebug() << "TimeToList(): MM: " << t_minute;
2765  qDebug() << "TimeToList(): SS: " << t_second;
2766 
2767  dhms.clear();
2768  dhms << t_day << t_hour << t_minute << t_second;
2769 }

4168 // Load US3 AUC Optima-derived data
4169 void US_XpnDataViewer::load_auc_xpn( )
4170 {
4171  //Disable if no connection to sys_data server
4172  if ( !check_sysdata_connection() )
4173  return;
4175 
4176  int status = 0;
4177  QStringList ifpaths;
4178 
4179  resetAll();
4180 
4181  QString dir = "";
4182  US_XpnRunAuc lddiag( dir );
4183  if ( lddiag.exec() == QDialog::Rejected )
4184  return;
4185 
4186  // Restore area beneath dialog
4187  qApp->processEvents();
4188 
4189  if ( dir.isEmpty() ) return;
4190 
4191  dir.replace( "\\", "/" ); // WIN32 issue
4192  if ( dir.right( 1 ) != "/" ) dir += "/"; // Ensure trailing '/'
4193 
4194  // Check the runID
4195  QString new_runID = dir.section( "/", -2, -2 ).simplified();
4196 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: runID" << new_runID;
4197 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: dir" << dir;
4198 
4199  QRegExp rx( "^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{1,80}$" );
4200  if ( rx.indexIn( new_runID ) < 0 )
4201  {
4202  QMessageBox::warning( this,
4203  tr( "Bad runID Name" ),
4204  tr( "The runID name may consist only of alphanumeric\n"
4205  "characters, the underscore, and the hyphen." ) );
4206  return;
4207  }
4208 
4209  // Set the runID and directory
4210  runID = new_runID;
4211  currentDir = dir;
4212  le_runID ->setText( runID );
4213  le_dir ->setText( currentDir );
4214 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: runID" << runID;
4215 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: dir" << currentDir;
4216 
4217  // Error reporting
4218  if ( status == US_DB2::NO_PROJECT )
4219  {
4220  QMessageBox::information( this,
4221  tr( "Attention" ),
4222  tr( "The project was not found.\n"
4223  "Please select an existing project and try again.\n" ) );
4224  }
4225 
4226  else if ( status != US_DB2::OK )
4227  {
4228  QMessageBox::information( this,
4229  tr( "Disk Read Problem" ),
4230  tr( "Could not read data from the disk.\n"
4231  "Disk status: " ) + QString::number( status ) );
4232  }
4233 
4234  // Load the AUC data
4235  le_status->setText( tr( "Reading AUC Xpn data ..." ) );
4236  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor) );
4237  QDir dirdir( dir, "*", QDir::Name, QDir::Files | QDir::Readable );
4238  dirdir.makeAbsolute();
4239  if ( dir.right( 1 ) != "/" ) dir += "/"; // Ensure trailing /
4240  xpn_fnames = dirdir.entryList( QStringList( "*.auc" ),
4241  QDir::Files, QDir::Name );
4242  xpn_fnames.sort();
4243  ntriple = xpn_fnames.size();
4244  cellchans.clear();
4245  lambdas .clear();
4246  triples .clear();
4247  int missm = 0;
4248 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: mwr ntriple" << ntriple;
4249 
4250  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ntriple; ii++ )
4251  {
4252  QString mwrfname = xpn_fnames.at( ii );
4253  QString mwrfpath = currentDir + mwrfname;
4254  ifpaths << mwrfpath;
4255  US_DataIO::RawData rdata;
4256 
4257  US_DataIO::readRawData( mwrfpath, rdata );
4258 
4259  allData << rdata;
4260 
4261  QString celchn = QString::number( rdata.cell ) + " / " +
4262  QString( rdata.channel );
4263  QString ccnode = mwrfname.section( ".", -4, -3 );
4264  QString celchnf = ccnode.replace( ".", " / " );
4265 
4266  if ( celchn != celchnf )
4267  {
4268 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: **F/D MISMATCH** " << celchn << celchnf << ii;
4269  celchn = celchnf;
4270  missm++;
4271  }
4272 
4273  int lambda = qRound( rdata.scanData[ 0 ].wavelength );
4274  QString triple = celchn + " / " + QString::number( lambda );
4275 
4276  if ( ! cellchans.contains( celchn ) )
4277  cellchans << celchn;
4278 
4279  if ( ! lambdas.contains( lambda ) )
4280  lambdas << lambda;
4281 
4282  if ( ! triples.contains( triple ) )
4283  triples << triple;
4284 
4285  le_status->setText( tr( "Data in for triple %1 of %2" )
4286  .arg( ii + 1 ).arg( ntriple ) );
4287  qApp->processEvents();
4288  }
4289 
4290  if ( missm > 0 )
4291  {
4292  QMessageBox::warning( this,
4293  tr( "Data/File Cell/Channel Mismatches" ),
4294  tr( "%1 mismatch(es) occurred in the Cell/Channel setting\n"
4295  " of AUC data versus File name nodes.\n\n"
4296  "The Cell/Channel settings have been corrected,\n"
4297  " but input data should be reviewed!!" )
4298  .arg( missm ) );
4299  }
4300 
4301  r_radii.clear();
4302  r_radii << allData[ 0 ].xvalues;
4303 
4304  isRaw = false;
4305  haveData = true;
4306  ncellch = cellchans .size();
4307  nlambda = lambdas .size();
4308  nscan = allData[ 0 ].scanCount();
4309  npoint = allData[ 0 ].pointCount();
4310  ntpoint = nscan * npoint;
4311 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: mwr ncellch nlambda nscan npoint"
4312  << ncellch << nlambda << nscan << npoint;
4313 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: rvS rvE" << r_radii[0] << r_radii[npoint-1];
4314  le_status->setText( tr( "All %1 raw AUCs have been loaded." )
4315  .arg( ntriple ) );
4316  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4317  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4318  qApp->processEvents();
4319 
4320  ct_from->setMaximum( nscan );
4321  ct_to ->setMaximum( nscan );
4322 
4323  xpn_data->load_auc( allData, ifpaths );
4324 
4325  QString tspath = currentDir + "/" + runID + ".time_state.tmst";
4326  haveTmst = QFile( tspath ).exists();
4327 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: load_auc complete";
4328  // Ok to enable some buttons now
4329  enableControls();
4330 DbgLv(1) << "RDa: enableControls complete";
4331 }

4426 // << "nscan" << nscan << allData[trpxs].scanCount();

4431  double* vv = vvec.data();
4432

4434  int scan_to = (int)ct_to ->value();

4442

4444  { // One-time build of X vector
4445  rr[ ptx ] = rdata->xvalues[ rdx ];
4446  }
4447 DbgLv(1) << "PltA: rr[n]" << rr[kpoint-1];
4448 
4449 // for ( int scnx = 0; scnx < nscan; scnx++ )
4450  for ( int scnx = 0; scnx < scan_knt; scnx++ )
4451  { // Build Y vector for each scan
4452  if ( excludes.contains( scnx ) ) continue;
4453 
4454  for ( int ptx = 0, rdx = radxs; ptx < kpoint; ptx++, rdx++ )
4455  {
4456  vv[ ptx ] = rdata->value( scnx, rdx );
4457  }
4458 
4459  if ( mcknt > 0 )
4460  {

4474  curv->setPen( pen_plot ); // Normal pen
4475  else
4476  curv->setPen( pen_red ); // Scan-focus pen

4527 void US_XpnDataViewer::changeCellCh( void )
4528 {
4529  // Match the description to find the correct triple in memory
4530  QString cellch = cb_cellchn->currentText();
4531 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: cellch" << cellch << "last_xmin" << last_xmin;
4532  if ( allData.size() < 1 )
4533  return;
4534 
4535  if ( last_xmin < 0.0 )
4536  { // If first time plotting any data, detect actual data bounds
4537  have_rngs = false;
4538  compute_ranges();
4539 
4540  int trxs = trpxs + lmbxs;
4541  int trxe = trpxs + lmbxe;
4542 
4543  last_xmin = allData[ trxs ].xvalues[ radxs ];
4544  last_xmax = last_xmin;
4545  US_DataIO::RawData* edata = &allData[ trxs ];
4546 
4547  for ( int rdx = radxs; rdx < radxe; rdx++ )
4548  {
4549  last_xmin = qMin( last_xmin, edata->xvalues[ rdx ] );
4550  last_xmax = qMax( last_xmax, edata->xvalues[ rdx ] );
4551  }
4552 
4553  last_ymin = allData[ trxs ].reading( 0, 0 );
4554  last_ymax = last_ymin;
4555 
4556  for ( int trx = trxs; trx < trxe; trx++ )
4557  { // Accumulate Y bounds, the amplitude bounds
4558  US_DataIO::RawData* edata = &allData[ trx ];
4559 
4560  for ( int scx = 0; scx < nscan; scx++ )
4561  {
4562  for ( int rdx = radxs; rdx < radxe; rdx++ )
4563  {
4564  last_ymin = qMin( last_ymin, edata->reading( scx, rdx ) );
4565  last_ymax = qMax( last_ymax, edata->reading( scx, rdx ) );
4566  }
4567  }
4568  }
4569 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: trxs trxe" << trxs << trxe;
4570  }
4571 
4572  else
4573  { // After first time, detect what has been already set
4574  QwtScaleDiv* sdx = AXISSCALEDIV( QwtPlot::xBottom );
4575  QwtScaleDiv* sdy = AXISSCALEDIV( QwtPlot::yLeft );
4576  last_xmin = sdx->lowerBound();
4577  last_xmax = sdx->upperBound();
4578  last_ymin = sdy->lowerBound();
4579  last_ymax = sdy->upperBound();
4580  }
4581 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: xmin xmax ymin ymax"
4582  << last_xmin << last_xmax << last_ymin << last_ymax;
4583 
4584  have_rngs = false;
4585  int lplrec = ntriple - 1;
4586 
4587  // Make sure cell/channel and plot record are in sync
4588  if ( ! isMWL )
4589  { // If plot record ranges are triples, point to first of cell/channel
4590  QString ccval = cb_cellchn->currentText().replace( " / ", "/" );
4591  QString ccplr = cb_pltrec->currentText().section( "/", 0, 1 );
4592 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: ccval" << ccval << "ccplr" << ccplr;
4593 
4594  if ( ccval != ccplr )
4595  {
4596  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ntriple; jj++ )
4597  {
4598  ccplr = triples[ jj ].section( "/", 0, 1 ).simplified()
4599  .replace( " / ", "/" );
4600 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: jj" << jj << "ccplr" << ccplr;
4601  if ( ccplr == ccval )
4602  { // Set plot record to first triple from cell/channel
4603  connect_ranges( false );
4604 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: set pltrec index" << jj;
4605  cb_pltrec->setCurrentIndex( jj );
4606  connect_ranges( true );
4607  break;
4608  }
4609  }
4610  }
4611  }
4612  else
4613  { // If plot record ranges are wavelengths, point to first wavelength
4614 DbgLv(1) << "chgCC: isMWL" << isMWL;
4615  lplrec = nlambda - 1;
4616 // connect_ranges( false );
4617 // cb_pltrec->setCurrentIndex( 0 );
4618 // connect_ranges( true );
4619  }
4620 
4621  compute_ranges();
4622  pb_prev ->setEnabled( ( recx > 0 ) );
4623  pb_next ->setEnabled( ( recx < lplrec ) );
4624 
4625 // changeRecord();
4626  plot_current();
4627 }

4866 // Compute the plot range indexes implied by current settings
4867 void US_XpnDataViewer::compute_ranges()
4868 {
4869  if ( have_rngs ) // If we just did this computation, return now
4870  return;
4871 
4872  ccx = cb_cellchn->currentIndex(); // Cell/Channel index
4873  rad_start = cb_rstart ->currentText().toDouble(); // Radius start
4874  rad_end = cb_rend ->currentText().toDouble(); // Radius end
4875  lmb_start = lambdas[ 0 ]; // Lambda start
4876  lmb_end = lambdas[ nlambda - 1 ]; // Lambda end
4877  recx = cb_pltrec ->currentIndex(); // Plot record index
4878  lmbxs = lambdas.indexOf( lmb_start ); // Lambda start index
4879  lmbxe = lambdas.indexOf( lmb_end ) + 1; // Lambda end index
4880  radxs = dvec_index( r_radii, rad_start ); // Radius start index
4881  radxe = dvec_index( r_radii, rad_end ) + 1; // Radius end index
4882 DbgLv(1) << "cmpR: rS rE rxS rxE" << rad_start << rad_end << radxs << radxe;
4883 DbgLv(1) << "cmpR: rvS rvE" << r_radii[radxs] << r_radii[radxe-1];
4884  klambda = lmbxe - lmbxs; // Count of plot lambdas
4885  kradii = radxe - radxs; // Count of plot radii
4886  kscan = nscan - excludes.size(); // Count included scans
4887  trpxs = ccx * nlambda; // Start triple index
4888  kpoint = kradii; // Count of plot points
4889  ktpoint = kscan * kpoint; // Total plot data points
4890 
4891  if ( isMWL )
4892  {
4893  trpxs += recx; // Triple-to-plot index
4894  }
4895  else
4896  {
4897  trpxs = recx; // Triple-to-plot index
4898  }
4899 // have_rngs = true; // Mark ranges computed
4900 DbgLv(1) << "cmpR: isMWL" << isMWL << "kpoint" << kpoint << "trpxs" << trpxs;
4901 }

4903 // Connect or Disconnect plot-range related controls
4904 void US_XpnDataViewer::connect_ranges( bool conn )
4905 {
4906  if ( conn )
4907  { // Connect the range-related controls
4908  connect( cb_cellchn, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
4909  this, SLOT ( changeCellCh( ) ) );
4910  connect( cb_rstart, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
4911  this, SLOT ( changeRadius( ) ) );
4912  connect( cb_rend, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
4913  this, SLOT ( changeRadius( ) ) );
4914  connect( cb_pltrec, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
4915  this, SLOT ( changeRecord( ) ) );
4916  }
4917 
4918  else
4919  { // Disconnect the range-related controls
4920  cb_cellchn->disconnect();
4921  cb_rstart ->disconnect();
4922  cb_rend ->disconnect();
4923  cb_pltrec ->disconnect();
4924  }
4925 }

5018 // Slot to export to openAUC
5019 void US_XpnDataViewer::export_auc()
5020 {
5021  if ( !isRaw )
5022  {
5023  int status = QMessageBox::information( this, tr( "Data Overwrite Warning..." ),
5024  tr( "This operation will overwrite all data currently in"
5025  "the same directory where these data were loaded from. Proceed? " ),
5026  tr( "&OK" ), tr( "&Cancel" ),
5027  0, 0, 1 );
5028  if ( status != 0 ) return;
5029  }
5030  QString runIDt = le_runID->text(); // User given run ID text
5031 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: runIDt" << runIDt;
5032 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: runID" << runID;
5033 
5034  if ( runIDt != runID )
5035  { // Set runID to new entry given by user
5036  QRegExp rx( "[^A-Za-z0-9_-]" ); // Possibly modify entry
5037  QString new_runID = runIDt;
5038  int pos = 0;
5039 
5040  while ( ( pos = rx.indexIn( new_runID ) ) != -1 )
5041  { // Loop thru any invalid characters given (not alphanum.,'_','-')
5042  new_runID.replace( pos, 1, "_" ); // Replace 1 char at pos
5043  }
5044 
5045 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: new_runID len" << new_runID.length();
5046  if ( new_runID.length() > 60 )
5047  {
5048  new_runID = QString( new_runID ).left( 52 )
5049  + QString( new_runID ).right( 8 );
5050 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: corr new_runID len" << new_runID.length();
5051 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: new_runID" << new_runID;
5052  }
5053 
5054  // Let the user know that the runID name has changed
5055  QMessageBox::warning( this,
5056  tr( "RunId Name Changed" ),
5057  tr( "The runId name has been changed."
5058  "\nNew runId:\n " ) + new_runID );
5059 
5060  runID = new_runID; // Show new run ID, dir.
5061  le_runID->setText( runID );
5062  currentDir = US_Settings::importDir() + "/" + runID;
5063  le_dir ->setText( currentDir );
5064  qApp->processEvents();
5065 
5066  xpn_data->set_run_values( runID, runType ); // Set run ID for export
5067  }
5068 
5069  // Export the AUC data to a local directory and build TMST
5070 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: BEFORE correct_radii() !!!!";
5071  correct_radii(); // Perform chromatic aberration radius corrections
5072 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: AFTER correct_radii() !!!!";
5073  int nfiles = xpn_data->export_auc( allData ); // Export AUC/TMST
5074 
5075  QString tspath = currentDir + "/" + runID + ".time_state.tmst";
5076  haveTmst = QFile( tspath ).exists();
5077 
5078  pb_showtmst->setEnabled( haveTmst );
5079  qApp->processEvents();
5080 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAuc: haveTmst" << haveTmst << "tmst file" << tspath;
5081 // int noptsy = cb_optsys->children().count();
5082  int noptsy = cb_optsys->count();
5083 DbgLv(1) << "ExpAucA: noptsy koptsy" << noptsy << cb_optsys->children().count();
5084 
5085  qDebug() << "Optical Systems Count: (noptsy) = " << cb_optsys->children().count();
5086 
5087  if ( noptsy > 1 )
5088  { // Export data from Optical Systems other than currently selected one
5089  int currsx = cb_optsys->currentIndex();
5090 
5091  for ( int osx = 0; osx < noptsy; osx++ )
5092  {
5093  if ( osx == currsx ) continue; // Skip already-handled opt sys
5094 
5095  cb_optsys->setCurrentIndex( osx );
5096  correct_radii(); // Chromatic aberration correction if needed
5097  int kfiles = xpn_data->export_auc( allData ) - 2; // Export data
5098  nfiles += kfiles; // Total files written
5099  }
5100 
5101  // Restore Optical System selection to what it was before
5102  cb_optsys->setCurrentIndex( currsx );
5103  }
5104 
5105  le_status ->setText( tr( "%1 AUC/TMST files written ..." ).arg( nfiles ) );
5106 }

5144 // Slot to handle click of Exclude Scan Range
5145 void US_XpnDataViewer::exclude_scans()
5146 {
5147  int scan_from = (int)ct_from->value();
5148  int scan_to = (int)ct_to ->value();
5149  int scan_knt = 1;
5150 
5151  for ( int scnx = 0; scnx < nscan; scnx++ )
5152  {
5153  if ( excludes.contains( scnx ) ) continue;
5154 
5155  if ( scan_knt >= scan_from && scan_knt <= scan_to )
5156  excludes << scnx;
5157 
5158  scan_knt++;
5159  }
5160 
5161  qSort( excludes );
5162  kscan = nscan - excludes.count();
5163 DbgLv(1) << "Excl: kscan" << kscan;
5164  ct_from ->disconnect();
5165  ct_to ->disconnect();
5166  ct_from ->setMaximum( kscan );
5167  ct_to ->setMaximum( kscan );
5168  connect( ct_from, SIGNAL( valueChanged( double ) ),
5169  this, SLOT ( exclude_from( double ) ) );
5170  connect( ct_to, SIGNAL( valueChanged( double ) ),
5171  this, SLOT ( exclude_to ( double ) ) );
5172  ct_to ->setValue( 0 );
5173  pb_include->setEnabled( true );
5174 }
5175 
5176 // Slot to handle click of Include All (restore of all scans)
5177 void US_XpnDataViewer::include_scans()
5178 {
5179  excludes.clear();
5180 
5181  kscan = nscan;
5182  ktpoint = kscan * kpoint;
5183 DbgLv(1) << "Incl: nscan" << nscan << "kscn ecnt" << kscan << excludes.count();
5184  ct_to ->setValue( 0 );
5185 // changeRecord(); // Force replot
5186  plot_current(); // Force replot
5187 
5188  ct_from ->disconnect();
5189  ct_to ->disconnect();
5190  ct_from ->setMaximum( kscan );
5191  ct_to ->setMaximum( kscan );
5192  connect( ct_from, SIGNAL( valueChanged( double ) ),
5193  this, SLOT ( exclude_from( double ) ) );
5194  connect( ct_to, SIGNAL( valueChanged( double ) ),
5195  this, SLOT ( exclude_to ( double ) ) );
5196  ct_to ->setValue( 0 );
5197  pb_include->setEnabled( false );
5198 }

5200 // Utility to find an index in a QVector<double> to a value epsilon match
5201 int US_XpnDataViewer::dvec_index( QVector< double >& dvec, const double dval )
5202 {
5203  const double eps = 1.e-4;
5204  double dmag = qAbs( dval);
5205 //DbgLv(1) << "dvix: dval dvknt" << dval << dvec.count();
5206 
5207  int indx = dvec.indexOf( dval ); // Try to find an exact match
5208 //DbgLv(1) << "dvix: dvec0 dval indx" << dvec[0] << dval << indx;
5209 
5210  if ( indx < 0 )
5211  { // If no exact match was found, look for a match within epsilon
5212 
5213  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dvec.size(); jj++ )
5214  { // Search doubles vector
5215  double ddif = qAbs( dvec[ jj ] - dval ) / dmag;
5216 //if(jj<3||(jj+4)>dvec.size())
5217 //DbgLv(1) << "dvix: jj" << jj << "dvj" << dvec[jj] << "ddif" << ddif;
5218 
5219  if ( ddif < eps )
5220  { // If vector value matches within epsilon, break and return
5221  indx = jj;
5222  break;
5223  }
5224  }
5225  }
5226 
5227 //DbgLv(1) << "dvix: dval" << dval << "indx" << indx;
5228  return indx;
5229 }

5252 // Slot to reload data
5253 void US_XpnDataViewer::reloadData()
5254 {
5255 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: in_reload" << in_reload;
5256  if ( in_reload ) // If already doing a reload,
5257  return; // skip starting a new one
5258 
5259  in_reload = true; // Flag in the midst of a reload
5260  int runix = runID.lastIndexOf( "-run" ) + 4;
5261  QString fRunId = runID.mid( runix );
5262  int iRunId = fRunId.toInt();
5263 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: runID" << runID << "runix" << runix << "iRunId" << iRunId;
5264  int scanmask = 1;
5265  scanmask = ( runType == "FI" ) ? 2 : scanmask;
5266  scanmask = ( runType == "IP" ) ? 4 : scanmask;
5267  scanmask = ( runType == "WI" ) ? 8 : scanmask;
5268 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: iRunId" << iRunId << "runType scanmask" << runType << scanmask;
5269 
5270 QDateTime sttime=QDateTime::currentDateTime();
5271  QString smsg = le_status->text();
5272  le_status->setText( tr( "Scanning Optima DB for any data updates..." ) );
5273  qApp->processEvents();
5274 
5275  // Import any newly added Scan Data records
5276  bool upd_ok = xpn_data->reimport_data( iRunId, scanmask );
5277 
5278  if ( ! upd_ok )
5279  { // No change in data scans: report inability to update
5280  nscan = allData[ trpxs ].scanCount();
5281 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: upd_ok" << upd_ok << "rlt_id" << rlt_id << "nscan" << nscan;
5282  if ( rlt_id == 0 ) // Output message only if not auto-reload
5283  {
5284  QMessageBox::warning( this,
5285  tr( "Reload Data Not Possible" ),
5286  tr( "The \"Reload Data\" action had no effect.\n"
5287  "No additional data has been recorded." ) );
5288  }
5289 
5290  if ( ! smsg.endsWith( tr( " scans)" ) ) )
5291  { // If need be, add scan count to the status message
5292  smsg = smsg + tr( " (%1 scans)" ).arg( nscan );
5293  le_status->setText( smsg );
5294  qApp->processEvents();
5295  }
5296 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: NO CHANGE";
5297  in_reload = false; // Flag no longer in the midst of reload
5298  return; // Return with no change in AUC data
5299  }
5300 double tm1=(double)sttime.msecsTo(QDateTime::currentDateTime())/1000.0;
5301 
5302  // Otherwise, report updated raw data import
5303  le_status->setText( tr( "Update of Raw Optima data import complete." ) );
5304  qApp->processEvents();
5305 
5306  // Now, update the AUC data with new scans
5307 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: build-raw started: tm1" << tm1;
5308  xpn_data->rebuild_rawData( allData );
5309 
5310 double tm2=(double)sttime.msecsTo(QDateTime::currentDateTime())/1000.0;
5311 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: build-raw done: tm1 tm2" << tm1 << tm2
5312  << "tm2i" << (tm2-tm1);
5313  // Reset scan counter maximum and report update complete
5314  nscan = allData[ trpxs ].scanCount();
5315  npoint = allData[ trpxs ].pointCount();
5316  ntpoint = nscan * npoint;
5317  ct_from->setMaximum( nscan );
5318  ct_to ->setMaximum( nscan );
5319  le_status->setText( tr( "Update of AUC data complete -- now %1 scans." )
5320  .arg( nscan ) );
5321  qApp->processEvents();
5322 
5323  // Do resets and re-plot the current triple
5324  changeCellCh();
5325  in_reload = false; // Flag no longer in the midst of reload
5326 }

5497  "Therefore, the boundary conditions are unknown and the experiment "
5498  "cannot be reliably analyzed. It fails GMP requirements and will "
5499  "therefore be aborted. The run will be deleted.\n\n"
5500  "The data can be retrieved with the \"View Raw Optima Data\" function "
5501  "in the UltraScan Utilities." ) );
5502 
5503 
5504  delete_autoflow_record();
5505  reset_auto();
5506  emit aborted_back_to_initAutoflow();
5507 
5508  return;
5509  }
5510 
5511  // QString mtitle_complete = tr( "Complete!" );
5512  // QString message_done = tr( "Experiment was completed. Optima data saved..." );
5513  // QMessageBox::information( this, mtitle_complete, message_done );
5514 
5515  updateautoflow_record_atLiveUpdate();
5516 
5517  reset_auto();
5518 
5519  in_reload_auto = false;
5520 
5521  //emit experiment_complete_auto( currentDir, ProtocolName, invID_passed, correctRadii ); // Updtade later: what should be passed with signal ??
5522  emit experiment_complete_auto( details_at_live_update );
5523 
5524  return;
5525  }
5526  }
5527 
5528  in_reload_auto = false; // Flag no longer in the midst of reload
5529 
5530  qDebug() << "Exit from reloaData with no change!";
5531 
5532  return; // Return with no change in AUC data
5533  }
5534 double tm1=(double)sttime.msecsTo(QDateTime::currentDateTime())/1000.0;
5535 
5536  // Otherwise, report updated raw data import
5537  le_status->setText( tr( "Update of Raw Optima data import complete." ) );
5538  qApp->processEvents();
5539 
5540  // Now, update the AUC data with new scans
5541 DbgLv(1) << "RLd: build-raw started: tm1" << tm1;
5542  xpn_data->rebuild_rawData( allData );
5543 
5544 double tm2=(double)sttime.msecsTo(QDateTime::currentDateTime())/1000.0;

5554  .arg( nscan ) );

5556

5558  changeCellCh();
5559 
5560  in_reload_auto = false; // Flag no longer in the midst of reload
5561 
5562  qDebug() << "Exit from reloaData with SOME change!";
5563 }

5584 // Slot to handle change in auto-reload check
5585 void US_XpnDataViewer::changeReload()
5586 {
5587 DbgLv(1) << "chgRld: checked" << ck_autorld->isChecked();
5588  if ( ck_autorld->isChecked() )
5589  { // Changing to checked: start the timer
5590  data_plot->replot();
5591 
5592  rlt_dlay = qRound( ct_rinterv->value() * 1000.0 );
5593  rlt_id = startTimer( rlt_dlay );
5594 DbgLv(1) << "chgRld: rlt_dlay" << rlt_dlay << "rlt_id" << rlt_id;
5595  }
5596 
5597  else
5598  { // Just been unchecked: stop the timer if need be
5599 DbgLv(1) << "chgRld: rlt_id" << rlt_id;
5600  if ( rlt_id != 0 )
5601  {
5602  killTimer( rlt_id );
5603 DbgLv(1) << "chgRld: STOPPED";
5604  }
5605  rlt_id = 0;
5606  in_reload = false;
5607  }
5608 }

5610 // Slot to handle change in auto-reload interval
5611 void US_XpnDataViewer::changeInterval()
5612 {

5614  if ( ! ck_autorld->isChecked() )
5615  { // If no auto reload checked, ignore this interval change for now
5616  rlt_id = 0;
5617  return;
5618  }
5619 
5620 DbgLv(1) << "chgInt: rlt_id" << rlt_id << "newInt" << ct_rinterv->value()
5621  << " " << QDateTime::currentDateTime().toString( "hh:mm:ss" );
5622  // Otherwise, stop the timer and then restart it with a new delay
5623  if ( rlt_id != 0 )
5624  {
5625  killTimer( rlt_id );
5626  }
5627 
5628  changeReload();
5629 }

5659 // Apply a chromatic aberration correction to auc data radius values <--- New function: uses lambdas/corr. from DB
5660 void US_XpnDataViewer::correct_radii()
5661 {
5662  const double rad_inc = 1e-5; // Radius precision
5663 
5664  char wktyp[ 3 ];
5665  strncpy( wktyp, allData[ 0 ].type, 2 );
5666  wktyp[ 2 ] = '\0';
5667  QString dtype = QString( wktyp );
5668 DbgLv(1) << "CR: dtype" << dtype << wktyp;
5669  if ( dtype == "IP" )
5670  {
5671 DbgLv(0) << "NO Chromatic Aberration correction for Interference data";
5672  return; // No correction for Interference data
5673  }
5674 
5675  int ntripl = allData.count();
5676  int npoint = allData[ 0 ].pointCount();
5677  double radval;
5678  QString fline;
5679  QVector <double> lambda;
5680  QVector <double> correction;
5681  lambda.clear();
5682  correction.clear();
5683 
5684  QString chromoArrayString;
5685  QStringList strl;
5686 
5687  chromoArrayString = currentInstrument["chromoab"].trimmed(); //<--- From DB
5688 
5689  if ( !chromoArrayString.isEmpty() )
5690  {
5691  strl = chromoArrayString.split(QRegExp("[\r\n\t ]+"));
5692 
5693  foreach (QString str, strl)
5694  {
5695  str.remove("(");
5696  str.remove(")");
5697 
5698  lambda.push_back( double( str.split(",")[0].trimmed().toFloat() ) );
5699  correction.push_back( double( str.split(",")[1].trimmed().toFloat() ) );
5700 
5701  qDebug() << str.split(",")[0].trimmed() << " " << str.split(",")[1].trimmed();
5702  }
5703  }
5704  // a correction was found
5705  if (correction.size() > 0)
5706  {
5707  if ( !auto_mode_bool )
5708  {
5709  int response=QMessageBox::question( this,
5710  tr( "Chromatic Aberration Correction:" ),
5711  tr( "Wavelength correction data for currently used Optima machine\n"
5712  "are found in DB and will be used to correct your data for\n"
5713  "chromatic aberration between 190 nm and 800 nm.\n\n"
5714  "Exported data will be modified!\n") );
5715  if (response == QMessageBox::No) return;
5716  }
5717  DbgLv(1) << "go ahead and correct...";
5718  // For each triple, get the wavelength; then compute and apply a correction
5719  for ( int jd = 0; jd < ntripl; jd++ )
5720  {
5721  int i=0;
5722  while ((int) lambda.at(i) != (int) allData[ jd ].scanData[ 0 ].wavelength)
5723  {
5724  i++; // Wavelength index
5725  if (i > 610) break;
5726  if (correction.at(i) != 0.0 )
5727  {
5728  for ( int jr = 0; jr < npoint; jr++ )
5729  { // Correct each radial point
5730  radval = r_radii[ jr ] - correction.at(i); // Corrected radius
5731  radval = qRound( radval / rad_inc ) * rad_inc; // Rounded
5732  allData[ jd ].xvalues[ jr ] = radval; // Replace radius
5733  }
5734  }
5735  }
5736  if (jd<3 || (jd+4)>ntripl )
5737  DbgLv(1) << "c_r: ri0 ro0" << r_radii[0] << allData[jd].xvalues[0]
5738  << "rin ron" << r_radii[npoint-1] << allData[jd].xvalues[npoint-1];
5739  }
5740  }
5741  else // No chromatic abberation in instrument's table
5742  {
5743  if ( auto_mode_bool )
5744  {
5745  correctRadii = QString("NO");
5746  }
5747  }
5748 }

5901 
5902 // Capture X range of latest Zoom and output meniscus profile
5903 void US_XpnDataViewer::currentRectf( QRectF rectf )
5904 {
5905  QVector< double > ascdat;
5906  QVector< int > srpms;
5907  QVector< int > ssfscs;
5908  QVector< int > sslscs;
5909  double radv1 = qRound( rectf.left() * 10000.0 ) * 0.0001;
5910  double radv2 = qRound( rectf.right() * 10000.0 ) * 0.0001;
5911  if ( radv2 > 7.0 )
5912  return; // Skip further processing if not reasonable zoom
5913  int irx1 = 0;
5914  int irx2 = 0;
5915  double kpoint = 0;
5916  QString cellch = cb_cellchn ->currentText();
5917  QString cech = QString( cellch ).replace( " / ", "" );
5918 
5919  QString impath = US_Settings::importDir() + "/" + runID;
5920  QDir dir;
5921  if ( ! dir.exists( impath ) )
5922  dir.mkpath( impath );
5923  QString dapath = impath + "/" + cech + ".wavelen.radpos.dat";
5924  QFile dafile( dapath );
5925  if ( !dafile.open( QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
5926  {
5927  return;
5928  }
5929  QTextStream datxto( &dafile );
5930 
5931  QString msg = tr( "%1, %2-to-%3 Radial adjustment scan..." )
5932  .arg( cellch ).arg( radv1 ).arg( radv2 );
5933  le_status->setText( msg );
5934  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor) );
5935  qApp->processEvents();
5936 DbgLv(1) << "cRect" << msg;
5937  datxto << "Wavelength,Meniscus\n";
5938 
5939  // Determine meniscus position for each wavelength of this channel
5940  for ( int jd = 0; jd < allData.count(); jd++ )
5941  {
5942  US_DataIO::RawData *rdata = &allData[ jd ];
5943 
5944  QString dchann = QString::number( rdata->cell )
5945  + QString( rdata->channel );
5946  if ( dchann != cech )
5947  continue;
5948 
5949  if ( irx2 == 0 )
5950  { // Get radial range indexes
5951  irx1 = US_DataIO::index( rdata, radv1 );
5952  irx2 = US_DataIO::index( rdata, radv2 );
5953  kpoint = irx2 - irx1 + 1;
5954  }
5955 
5956  double wavelen = rdata->scanData[ 0 ].wavelength; // Wavelength
5957 
5958  // Create an average scan value vector for the search range
5959  int nscan = rdata->scanCount();
5960  double afact = 1.0 / (double)nscan;
5961  ascdat.fill( 0.0, kpoint );
5962  int prrpm = 0; // Previous speed
5963  int nspeed = 0;
5964  int ssx = 0;
5965 
5966  for ( int js = 0; js < nscan; js++ )
5967  {
5968  US_DataIO::Scan* dscan = &rdata->scanData[ js ];
5969 
5970  // Save changed speed and each one's scan start,end indecies
5971  int ssrpm = (int)qRound( dscan->rpm * 0.01 ) * 100;
5972  if ( ssrpm != prrpm )
5973  { // Speed changes from previous: add to speed list
5974  srpms << ssrpm;
5975  ssfscs << js;
5976  sslscs << js;
5977  ssx = nspeed;
5978  prrpm = ssrpm;
5979  nspeed++;
5980  }
5981  else
5982  { // Same speed as previous scan: update last index
5983  sslscs[ ssx ] = js;
5984  }
5985 
5986  // Accumulate average scan for the current channel
5987  for ( int jr = 0; jr < kpoint; jr++ )
5988  {
5989  ascdat[ jr ] += dscan->rvalues[ jr + irx1 ] * afact;
5990  }
5991  }
5992 
5993  // Find the position of the minimum average-scan value in the range
5994  double rvmin = 1.0e+99;
5995  int irpos = -1;
5996  for ( int jr = 0; jr < kpoint; jr++ )
5997  {
5998  double rval = ascdat[ jr ];
5999  if ( rval < rvmin )
6000  {
6001  rvmin = rval;
6002  irpos = jr;
6003  }
6004  }
6005 
6006  // Meniscus radius value for the wavelength
6007  double radiusw = rdata->xvalues[ irpos + irx1 ];
6008 DbgLv(1) << " wavelen/radpos: " << wavelen << " / " << radiusw;
6009 
6010  // Output a wavelength,radial-position line
6011  QString outline = QString::number( wavelen ) + ","
6012  + QString().asprintf( "%.3f", radiusw ) + "\n";
6013  datxto << outline;
6014  } // END: datasets loop
6015  dafile.close();
6016 
6017  int nspeed = srpms.count();
6018 
6019  if ( nspeed > 1 )
6020  { // If multi-speed, add search/output as "wavelen/speed/radpos"
6021  QVector< int > wvlns;
6022  QVector< double > menrads;
6023  QString dapath = impath + "/" + cech + ".wavelen.speeds-meniscus.dat";
6024  QFile dafile( dapath );
6025  dafile.open( QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text );
6026  QTextStream datxto( &dafile );
6027  QString outline = tr( "Wavelength" );
6028 
6029  for ( int jq = 0; jq < nspeed; jq++ )
6030  { // Add speeds to header line
6031  outline += "," + QString::number( srpms[ jq ] );
6032  }
6033  outline += "\n";
6034  datxto << outline;
6035 
6036  for ( int jd = 0; jd < allData.count(); jd++ )
6037  { // Get information for each dataset
6038  US_DataIO::RawData *rdata = &allData[ jd ];
6039 
6040  QString dchann = QString::number( rdata->cell )
6041  + QString( rdata->channel );
6042  if ( dchann != cech )
6043  continue;
6044 
6045  if ( irx2 == 0 )
6046  { // Get radial range indexes
6047  irx1 = US_DataIO::index( rdata, radv1 );
6048  irx2 = US_DataIO::index( rdata, radv2 );
6049  kpoint = irx2 - irx1 + 1;
6050  }
6051 
6052  int wavelen = (int)rdata->scanData[ 0 ].wavelength; // Wavelength
6053  wvlns << wavelen;
6054 
6055  // Start data line with wavelength value
6056  outline = QString::number( wavelen );
6057 
6058  for ( int jq = 0; jq < nspeed; jq++ )
6059  {
6060  // Create an average scan value vector for the search range
6061  int irpm = srpms [ jq ];
6062  int jsf = ssfscs[ jq ];
6063  int jsl = sslscs[ jq ] + 1;
6064  int nscan = jsl - jsf;
6065  double afact = 1.0 / (double)nscan;
6066 DbgLv(1) << " MSPD: jq" << jq << "speed" << irpm << "jsf,jsl,nsc" << jsf << jsl << nscan;
6067  ascdat.fill( 0.0, kpoint );
6068  for ( int js = jsf; js < jsl; js++ )
6069  { // Average scans in the current speed step
6070  US_DataIO::Scan* dscan = &rdata->scanData[ js ];
6071 
6072  for ( int jr = 0; jr < kpoint; jr++ )
6073  {
6074  ascdat[ jr ] += dscan->rvalues[ jr + irx1 ] * afact;
6075  }
6076  }
6077 
6078  // Find the position of the minimum value in the range
6079  double rvmin = 1.0e+99;
6080  int irpos = -1;
6081  for ( int jr = 0; jr < kpoint; jr++ )
6082  {
6083  double rval = ascdat[ jr ];
6084  if ( rval < rvmin )
6085  {
6086  rvmin = rval;
6087  irpos = jr;
6088  }
6089  }
6090 
6091  double radiusw = rdata->xvalues[ irpos + irx1 ];
6092  menrads << radiusw;
6093 DbgLv(1) << " wavelen/speed/radpos: " << wavelen
6094  << " / " << irpm << " / " << radiusw << " irpos" << irpos;
6095 
6096  outline += "," + QString::number( radiusw );
6097  } // END: speed loop
6098  outline += "\n";
6099  datxto << outline;
6100  } // END: dataset loop
6101 
6102  dafile.close();
6103 
6104  // Now output a transformed data file (speed in rows instead of columns)
6105  dapath = impath + "/" + cech + ".speed.wavelens-meniscus.dat";
6106  QFile dafile2( dapath );
6107  dafile2.open( QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text );
6108  QTextStream datxto2( &dafile2 );
6109  outline = tr( "Speed" );
6110  int nwvlen = wvlns.count();
6111 
6112  for ( int jw = 0; jw < nwvlen; jw++ )
6113  { // Add wavelengths to header line
6114  outline += "," + QString::number( wvlns[ jw ] );
6115  }
6116  outline += "\n";
6117  datxto2 << outline;
6118 
6119  for ( int js = 0; js < nspeed; js++ )
6120  { // Compose speed,meniscus,meniscus... rows
6121  // Start data line with speed value
6122  outline = QString::number( srpms[ js ] );
6123  int jv = js;
6124 
6125  for ( int jq = 0; jq < nwvlen; jq++, jv += nspeed )
6126  { // append meniscus values for each column
6127  outline += "," + QString().sprintf( "%.3f", menrads[ jv ] );
6128  }
6129  outline += "\n";
6130  datxto2 << outline;
6131  } // END: speed loop
6132 
6133  dafile2.close();
6134 
6135  } // END: multi-speed
6136 
6137  le_status->setText( tr( "%1 Radial adjustment scan complete." )
6138  .arg( cech ) );
6139  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
6140  qApp->processEvents();
6141 }
